def: A fish; the ruff. Pope Joan, a game at cards played on a roundboard with compartments.-- Pope's eye, the gland surrounded with fat in the middle of thethigh of an ox or sheep. R. D. Blackmore.-- Pope's nose, the rump, or uropygium, of a bird. See Uropygium.
Having a tendency to form ulcers; rendering ulcerous.
Easily or clearly seen; distinctly visible; perspicuous. [Obs.]Testament of Love.
A genus of fresh-water air-breathing mollusks, abundant inponds and streams; -- called also pond snail. [Written also Lymn√¶a.]
One who practices sleight of hand; a prestidigitator.
Capable of being changed from a liquid to a solid state. [Obs.]They formed a . . . fixed concrescible oil. Fourcroy (Trans. ).
